abstract: Video of safety test conducted by Trinity Industries on its guardrail system appears to show that crash resulted in more extensive damage to car than in previous tests, raising concerns about risk posed to car's occupants; federal officials say it will take weeks to analyze results of test.
lead_paragraph: The test, the last in a series ordered by the Federal Highway Administration, appeared to be the first to shed doubt on the widely used barrier system.

byline.original: By DANIELLE IVORY and AARON M. KESSLER

snippet: The test, the last in a series ordered by the Federal Highway Administration, appeared to be the first to shed doubt on the widely used barrier system.

headline.main: Assessment of Guardrails May Hinge on Final Crash Test
